The paper deals with the problem of classifying entities in a semantic graph, which involves machine learning and natural language processing techniques. This suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is a popular technique in deep learning, further supporting the possibility of it belonging to cs.LG. The paper also deals with the extraction of features from data, which is a common problem in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the Semantic Web, which involves the use of ontologies and knowledge representation, suggesting that it could belong to the Semantic Web (cs.SI) sub-category.
